What is Power BI, and what are its three main components?
Power BI is a data visualization and business intelligence tool by Microsoft.
Main components: Power BI Desktop, Power BI Service, Power BI Mobile.

Name two business use cases for Power BI dashboards.

Sales performance analysis

Financial reporting

How do you download and install Power BI Desktop?
Go to powerbi.microsoft.com, download Power BI Desktop, and follow the installation steps.

What is the difference between Power BI Desktop and Power BI Service?
Desktop is for creating reports; Service is for sharing and viewing reports online.

What file extension does a Power BI project use?
.pbix

Explain the role of Power Query in Power BI.
Power Query is used to connect, clean, and transform data before analysis.

Why would a business prefer Power BI over Excel for reporting?
Interactive visuals, real-time data, better scalability, and automation.

Describe one limitation of the free version of Power BI.
You can't share reports via Power BI Service.

What is a "published report" in Power BI Service?
A report uploaded from Power BI Desktop to the cloud for sharing and access.

How does Power BI Mobile enhance accessibility?
It lets users view and interact with reports on phones and tablets.

Compare Power BI with Tableauâ€”pros and cons.
Power BI: Cheaper, Microsoft-friendly
Tableau: More advanced visuals, higher cost

Explain how Power BI integrates with Azure services.
It connects to Azure SQL, Synapse, ML, and Active Directory for secure and advanced analytics.

What are "gateways" in Power BI, and when are they needed?
Gateways connect on-premise data sources to Power BI Service; used for scheduled refreshes.

How would you convince a company to adopt Power BI?
It improves decision-making, saves time, increases ROI with better insights.

What security features does Power BI offer for sensitive data?
Row-level security, encryption, Azure AD integration, and data access control
